de.lmu.ifi.dbs.jfeaturelib

Class LibProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.utilities.properties.PropertyContainer
      • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.jfeaturelib.LibProperties

  • public class LibProperties
extends de.lmu.ifi.dbs.utilities.properties.PropertyContainer
    The property wrapper class for jfeaturelib.properties. This class is used to access the properties of jfeaturelib.properties in an easier way without having to request keys by magic strings. For example in order to obtain the value of sift.binary, you can request LibProperties.get().getFile(LibProperties.SIFT_BINARY).
    Author:
    graf
    See Also:
    PropertyContainer

      • LibProperties

        public LibProperties()
        Initializes an empty properties set. You should know what you are doing as the needed Properties will not be present. So all required properties have to be set before it is passed to an extractor/descriptor.
